typo hard-cord

LED Service Name --> xyz.openbmc_project.LED.GroupManager

well, it's not about a style.. It's really about taking care of handling this object irrespective of which service implements it.
Ack
hmm.. why is this a template ?.. we are anyway doing a mapper-get-service to know who implements xyz.openbmc_project.Led.Group interface .. what problem is solved by having a template here ?
Because we need to make a callback when we get the `service Name`.

hmm.. why is it doing for "enclosure_identify_blink" ?.. the original code had a priority order ..  

if enclosure_identify_blink --> then do ..
else check if enclosure_identfy --> then do..

but this is breaking that hierarchy.. Same goes for all the instances where this is referenced in this file.
Ack
please remove this comment .. This commit is actually putting this support
Ack
getLEDService ?
Done

please put "enclosure_identify" into previous line ?.

Also, this one is missing getLEDService
Done
I don't think we want to return an error here because the enclosure_identify_blink will be passed first, and when not present, mapper will return an error and cause this whole thing to fail.

Sure
Done

I don't think it's this simple. With your fix, we'll now just never call your callback handler. The second path that works is embedded in the callback which will not be called now. Can you be sure to post some tested results in the commit message ensuring you've tested this path (enclosure_identify_blink not present but enclosure_identify is)?
sure, i see, let me fix it.

You're going to get 2 responses now:

a{sas} 2 
"xyz.openbmc_project.LED.GroupManager"
 4 "org.freedesktop.DBus.Introspectable" "org.freedesktop.DBus.ObjectManager" "org.freedesktop.DBus.Peer" "org.freedesktop.DBus.Properties" 

"xyz.openbmc_project.ObjectMapper" 
3 "org.freedesktop.DBus.Introspectable" "org.freedesktop.DBus.Peer" "org.freedesktop.DBus.Properties

I wonder if it's fair to assume the first one will always be the "correct" service? What happens if xyz.openbmc_project.ObjectMapper happens to be first?

What happens if the two LED objects are hosted in different services?
